Rabia Sude Karakoç
Subsystems & Implementation Details:

•	Strategy Design Pattern Framework: Engineered the extensible architectural sorting framework under the com.smarttravel.strategy ecosystem to cleanly decouple sorting algorithms 
from the main application logic. Designed the foundational SortStrategy abstract abstraction interface. Developed three concrete implementation classes—SortByName, SortByPopulation, 
and SortByArea—utilizing Java’s native Comparator mechanisms and Collections.sort(). This design allows the platform to dynamically swap sorting criteria at runtime based on real-time 
user selections within the combo box, satisfying the project's non-functional extensibility requirements. 
•	Custom Iterator Architecture for Data Filtering: Designed and finalized the custom behavioral data streaming layer within the com.smarttravel.iterator package to filter geographic
datasets dynamically. Developed the foundational WeatherIterator control interface defining sequential operations. Programmed four distinct concrete iterator 
implementations—SunnyIterator, RainyIterator, CloudyIterator, and SnowyIterator. Configured their constructors to ingest the global city repository list and executed lookup pointer logic to iteratively skip elements that do not match the target meteorological state, enabling the GUI to execute seamless, pattern-driven conditional views. 
•	Observer Pattern & Multi-Threaded Live Simulation: Conceptualized and built the complete Publisher-Subscriber (Observer) architecture to handle concurrent data streaming. 
Designed the WeatherReportProvider as the core Subject that manages subscription hooks and dynamically broadcasts real-time updates to registered visual components. Implemented a background concurrency layer utilizing an independent worker thread running an infinite execution loop with controlled delays (Thread.sleep(3000)). This thread automatically mutates city weather states randomly every 3 seconds and invokes the notification chain, keeping the UI data-fresh without locking the primary user interface thread. 
•	Live Analytics Dashboard Visualization: Spearheaded the development of the live graphical data processing layers. Implemented the dynamic Bar Chart components to monitor 
live temperature fluctuations across the entire city database, and the Pie Chart panels to calculate and illustrate the percentage distribution of active weather states across 
the ecosystem. Registered these analytical sub-panels as active concrete observers to the WeatherReportProvider, achieving fully automatic and seamless chart updates upon every 
cycle of the background simulation thread.

